cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV. 

This paper discusses the use of deep pre-trained bidirectional transformers for natural language processing tasks, specifically for multi-sentence scoring. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses pre-training strategies and transformer architectures, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The tasks evaluated in the paper involve pairwise comparisons between sequences, which could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions the use of transformers for natural language understanding, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
